<p>
  This unit deals with projectile motion.
  Projectile motion occurs whenver you throw an object up into the air.
  Examples of projectile motion are shooting a basketball,
  hitting a volleyball,
  firing an arrow,
  or jumping off of a diving broad.
</p>

<p>
  The most important single fact about projectile motion is this:
  All 2-dimensional projecitle motion
  takes the shape of a <strong>downward parabola</strong>.
  (The only exceptions are if an object is dropped down or thrown directly upward.
  These exceptions are 1-dimensional projectile motion.)
</p>


