<p>
  The most important point of a downward parabola
  is the <strong>vertex</strong>.
  The vertex is at the top of the parabola.
  In the above graphs, the vertex is marked with a black circle.
  For an object in projectile motion,
  the vertex represents the point at which the object is at its highest point.
</p>

<p>
  Note that a parabola is <strong>not</strong>
  the same as an exponential function!
  Many students confuse these.
  An exponential function increases at a much faster rate and
  decreases to an asymptote. An exponential function is monotonically
  increasing and does not include a vertex.
</p>

